    "body": "### Steps to reproduce\r\n1. Visit a site with nested scrolling elements like maps.google.com or reddit.com when it has it's (terrible) app banner.\r\n2. Try to scroll vertically.\r\n\r\n### Expected results\r\n- The toolbar shows and hides or is permanently visible when scrolling vertically.\r\n\r\n### Actual results\r\n- The scroll bar is hidden entirely and the toolbar cannot be accessed until the page is removed.\r\n\r\nIn the Google Maps example below, you lose access to the toolbar and tab counter if it's scrolled away.\r\nIn the Reddit example, you lose the toolbar and tab counter too, but you can access it if you dismiss the (terrible) app banner.\r\n\r\nhttps://user-images.githubusercontent.com/1370580/129980956-5f4bdc56-bd98-4a3e-a6a6-6f6f9cb21000.mp4\r\n\r\n\r\nhttps://user-images.githubusercontent.com/1370580/129980968-a68a4020-e111-432a-980e-2efd21302486.mp4\r\n\r\n",
